g.springframework.boot:spring-boot-security:4.1.0/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-26T21-48-40-253782Z.log` wrote a post-gen intervention report that classifies the stage as `metadata_fix_failed`, and `logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-security:4.1.0/metadata-fix/codex.log` ends mid reproduce/fix loop without a verified green run.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-security:4.1.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T21-25-24-504603Z.log`\n- `logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-security:4.1.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T21-49-44-905004Z.log`\n- `logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-security:4.1.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n- `logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-security:4.1.0/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-26T21-48-40-253782Z.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Check out the preserved branch and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-security:4.1.0` to confirm the current native failure.\n2. Complete `metadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-security/4.1.0/reachability-metadata.json` so Spring Boot Security auto-configuration can read the required `.class` resources / condition types in native image.\n3. Rerun the targeted library test and refresh stats/metrics once the native test passes."}}
